notes.title: What are Typed Array in Node JS?
notes.content:
## Array Buffers in Node JS

`Array Buffers` are an array of bytes. It means that it is like array i.e. contiguous memory location. **Each Index** can hold data of 1 byte. The maximum alloted size by Node JS is nearly equal to 2 Gib.
